2. But if this general may not be granted, we proceed to particulars, and ſay, that it is lawful to ſubmit to the tryal of our abilities, faith and manners by thoſe that ſhall be deputed thereto by authority. This ſeems to be implyed in that Command,1 Pet. 3.15
〈 in non-Latin alphabet 〉 . If to every one that ask, then much more to thoſe in authority. If they ask, and if of our hope, then of our faith and life, which are the foundation of our hope. And this ſeems to be no more, then what our Lord Jeſus, Peter, Paul;
and other Saints have ſubmitted to before us.
